{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-10",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_10_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "10 - The Lobster Quadrille",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.759,
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 0.48,
  "page_end_sec": 249.52,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.48,
      "end": 4.68,
      "text": "Chapter 10 of Alice's Adventures in Wonderland by Lewis Carroll"
    },
    {
      "start": 5.14,
      "end": 7.14,
      "text": "The Lobster Quadrille"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.09,
      "end": 11.9,
      "text": "The Mock Turtle sighed deeply, and drew",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 11.9,
      "end": 13.96,
      "text": "the back of one flapper across his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.4,
      "end": 16.5,
      "text": "He looked at Alice, and tried to speak,"
    },
    {
      "start": 16.64,
      "end": 19.24,
      "text": "but for a minute or two sobs choked his voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.024,
      "end": 22.52,
      "text": "\"Same as if he had a bone in his throat,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 22.7,
      "end": 23.66,
      "text": "said the Gryphon:"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.72,
      "end": 26.4,
      "text": "and it set to work shaking him and punching him in the back."
    },
    {
      "start": 27.36,
      "end": 29.5,
      "text": "At last the Mock Turtle recovered his voice,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 29.66,
      "end": 31.52,
      "text": "and with tears running down his cheeks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.62,
      "end": 32.22,
      "text": "went on again:"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.0,
      "end": 36.5,
      "text": "\"You may not have lived much under the sea--\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 37.6,
      "end": 38.26,
      "text": "(\"I haven't,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 38.26,
      "end": 38.78,
      "text": "said Alice)"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.68,
      "end": 43.7,
      "text": "\"and perhaps you were never even introduced to a lobster--\""
    },
    {
      "start": 44.704,
      "end": 45.7,
      "text": "(Alice began to say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.82,
      "end": 46.98,
      "text": "\"I once tasted----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 47.84,
      "end": 49.76,
      "text": "but checked herself hastily, and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.12,
      "end": 50.56,
      "text": "\"No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.74,
      "end": 51.06,
      "text": "never\")"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.48,
      "end": 54.86,
      "text": "\"--so you can have no idea what a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 54.86,
      "end": 58.16,
      "text": "delightful thing a Lobster Quadrille is!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 59.36,
      "end": 59.7,
      "text": "\"No,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 59.82,
      "end": 60.06,
      "text": "indeed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.46,
      "end": 60.98,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 61.52,
      "end": 62.7,
      "text": "\"What sort of a dance is it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 63.82,
      "end": 64.4,
      "text": "\"Why,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 64.7,
      "end": 65.4,
      "text": "said the Gryphon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.5,
      "end": 68.1,
      "text": "\"you first form into a line along the sea-shore----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 69.14,
      "end": 69.76,
      "text": "\"Two lines!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 70.06,
      "end": 71.18,
      "text": "cried the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 71.42,
      "end": 72.32,
      "text": "\"Seals,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.32,
      "end": 72.72,
      "text": "turtles,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.82,
      "end": 73.64,
      "text": "and so on;"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.88,
      "end": 76.26,
      "text": "then when you've cleared the jelly-fish"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.44,
      "end": 77.22,
      "text": "out of the way----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 77.42,
      "end": 79.54,
      "text": "\"_That_ generally takes some time,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 79.64,
      "end": 80.84,
      "text": "interrupted the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.48,
      "end": 82.72,
      "text": "\"--you advance twice----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 84.5,
      "end": 85.94,
      "text": "\"each with a lobster as a partner!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 86.2,
      "end": 87.0,
      "text": "cried the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.96,
      "end": 88.34,
      "text": "\"Of course,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 88.76,
      "end": 89.72,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 90.4,
      "end": 91.48,
      "text": "\"advance twice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.288,
      "end": 93.3,
      "text": "set to partners----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 94.528,
      "end": 97.02,
      "text": "\"--change lobsters, and retire in same order,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 97.18,
      "end": 98.24,
      "text": "continued the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.63,
      "end": 100.28,
      "text": "\"Then,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 100.28,
      "end": 100.76,
      "text": "you know,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 101.28,
      "end": 102.34,
      "text": "the Mock Turtle went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.04,
      "end": 105.12,
      "text": "\"you throw the----\""
    },
    {
      "start": 105.22,
      "end": 106.3,
      "text": "\"The lobsters!\" shouted the Gryphon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 106.32,
      "end": 107.5,
      "text": "with a bound into the air."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.64,
      "end": 110.92,
      "text": "\"--as far out to sea as you can----\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 111.16,
      "end": 112.22,
      "text": "\"Swim, after them!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 112.4,
      "end": 113.38,
      "text": "screamed the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.46,
      "end": 116.42,
      "text": "\"Turn a somersault in the sea!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 116.82,
      "end": 118.06,
      "text": "cried the Mock Turtle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.28,
      "end": 119.46,
      "text": "capering wildly about."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.48,
      "end": 121.52,
      "text": "\"Change lobsters again!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 121.84,
      "end": 122.64,
      "text": "yelled the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.86,
      "end": 125.02,
      "text": "\"Back to land again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 125.38,
      "end": 128.74,
      "text": "and--that's all the first figure,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 129.88,
      "end": 130.64,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.8,
      "end": 132.12,
      "text": "suddenly dropping his voice;"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.24,
      "end": 134.82,
      "text": "and the two creatures, who had been jumping about"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.06,
      "end": 136.72,
      "text": "like mad things all this time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.84,
      "end": 139.62,
      "text": "sat down again very sadly and quietly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.82,
      "end": 140.64,
      "text": "and looked at Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.6,
      "end": 144.18,
      "text": "\"It must be a very pretty dance,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 144.5,
      "end": 145.72,
      "text": "said Alice, timidly."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.76,
      "end": 148.8,
      "text": "\"Would you like to see a little of it?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 149.32,
      "end": 149.98,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.32,
      "end": 151.9,
      "text": "\"Very much indeed,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 152.3,
      "end": 152.86,
      "text": "said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 153.58,
      "end": 154.16,
      "text": "\"Come,"
    },
    {
      "start": 154.26,
      "end": 156.18,
      "text": "let's try the first figure!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 156.52,
      "end": 158.34,
      "text": "said the Mock Turtle to the Gryphon."
    },
    {
      "start": 159.12,
      "end": 161.32,
      "text": "\"We can do it without lobsters,"
    },
    {
      "start": 161.32,
      "end": 161.74,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.656,
      "end": 163.68,
      "text": "Which shall sing?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 165.28,
      "end": 167.8,
      "text": "\"Oh, _you_ sing,\" said the Gryphon. \"I've forgotten the words.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 169.28,
      "end": 172.44,
      "text": "So they began solemnly dancing round and round Alice,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 172.44,
      "end": 175.24,
      "text": "every now and then treading on her toes when they passed"
    },
    {
      "start": 175.24,
      "end": 178.3,
      "text": "too close, and waving their forepaws to mark the time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.3,
      "end": 181.74,
      "text": "while the Mock Turtle sang this, very slowly and sadly:--"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.26,
      "end": 187.64,
      "text": "\"Will you walk a little faster?\" said a whiting to a snail,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 187.64,
      "end": 192.82,
      "text": "\"There's a porpoise close behind us, and he's treading on my tail."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.82,
      "end": 197.68,
      "text": "See how eagerly the lobsters and the turtles all advance!"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.42,
      "end": 202.8,
      "text": "They are waiting on the shingle--will you come and join the dance?"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.62,
      "end": 207.7,
      "text": "Will you, won't you, will you, won't you, will you join the dance?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 208.54,
      "end": 212.6,
      "text": "Will you, won't you, will you, won't you, won't you join the dance?"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.56,
      "end": 217.8,
      "text": "\"You can really have no notion how delightful it will be,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 218.38,
      "end": 222.92,
      "text": "When they take us up and throw us, with the lobsters, out to sea!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 223.68,
      "end": 228.64,
      "text": "But the snail replied: \"Too far, too far!\" and gave a look askance--",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 229.408,
      "end": 234.06,
      "text": "Said he thanked the whiting kindly, but he would not join the dance."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.94,
      "end": 239.24,
      "text": "Would not, could not, would not, could not, would not join the dance.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 239.36,
      "end": 244.4,
      "text": "Would not, could not, would not, could not, could not join the dance."
    },
    {
      "start": 245.5,
      "end": 247.72,
      "text": "\"What matters it how far we go?\" his scaly friend replied;",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 247.94,
      "end": 249.52,
      "text": "\"There is another shore, you know, upon the other side."
    }
  ]
}
